docker-compose.yml
nakama-config.yml
Makefile
```

## Commands

```bash
# Backend
cd backend && go test ./... -v          # Run Go tests
go build -buildmode=plugin -trimpath -o ./backend.so  # Build plugin

# Frontend
cd frontend && npm install              # Install deps
cd frontend && npm run dev              # Dev server (port 5173)
cd frontend && npx vitest run           # Run tests

# Full stack
make dev                                # Docker Compose up (Nakama + PostgreSQL)
make build                              # Build plugin + frontend
make test                               # All tests
```

## Code Style

### Go (Backend)
- Pure game logic functions MUST NOT depend on Nakama runtime types
- All RPC handlers MUST check `isRegisteredUser` before gated operations
- Match handlers follow Nakama interface: MatchInit, MatchJoinAttempt, MatchJoin, MatchLoop, MatchLeave, MatchTerminate
- Structured logging via `logger.Info/Warn/Error` with fields

### TypeScript (Frontend)
- nakama-js SDK is the sole transport layer — no direct fetch/WebSocket calls
- Client MUST NOT derive game state locally — render server-broadcast data only
- Component structure: pages/ for routes, components/ for reusable UI, hooks/ for state logic

## Constitution Reference

See `.specify/memory/constitution.md` (v2.1.0) for binding principles:
- **I. Server Authority** (NON-NEGOTIABLE): All game logic server-side
- **II. WebSocket-First**: Game events via WS, REST for RPCs only
- **III. Match Isolation**: Goroutine-per-match, no shared state
- **IV. Test-Driven**: TDD for checkWin/checkDraw/applyMove
- **V. Containerized**: Docker Compose parity local ↔ production
- **VI. Mobile-First**: 375px+ responsive, Tailwind + shadcn/ui
- **VII. Disconnect = Forfeit**: Immediate, no reconnection grace period

